# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<---- 72 chars max ----------------------------------->|
#
# Types: feat, fix, refactor, perf, docs, test, build, ci, chore
#
# Scopes (optional but encouraged):
#   app boundary: frontend, backend, shared
#   feature area: auth, typing, leaderboard, api, db, redis, cache
#   other:        deps, release
#
# Subject rules:
#   - imperative mood: "add x" not "added x"
#   - lowercase first word
#   - no trailing period
#   - describe the change, not the file
#   - if you need "and", split into two commits

# --- Why did you make this change? (body, optional) ---
#
# Explain the motivation, hidden constraints, or trade-offs.
# The diff shows WHAT changed. This explains WHY.
# Wrap at 72 characters.

# --- Footer (optional) ---
# Refs #<issue>
# Closes #<issue>
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
